Keyword enemy~
Level 0
Text
Name       : enemy
Synopsis   : enemy -r|-f <nickname> <comment>

This list is for your enemies.  If you don't want to receive express messages
from someone, just put his/her name into this list.  Optional part lets you
write a comment upto 60 characters about the user.  You can use -r to remove
a user from your enemy list.  Maximum number of enemies that you can put into
your list is 50.  -f option is used to completely delete your enemy list.

Examples: enemy deneme example (puts user Deneme into your enemy list)
          enemy -r deneme      (removes user Deneme from your enemy list)
          enemy -f             (completely deletes your enemy list)
          enemy                (prints your enemies to the screen)
~
End
Keyword ignore~
Level 0
Text
Name      : ignore
Synopsis  : ignore -r|-f <nickname> <comment>

Similar to the enemy list, you can ignore the notes of people by putting them
into this list. "list" and "new" commands will not show their notes in any
way.  However, you can still read the notes of someone from your ignore list
with "read", "previous", and "next" commands. Maximum comment length is 60
charactersand list can take at most 50 users.
PS: Forum Moderators; your ignore list will not be checked in your forum.

Examples: ignore deneme example (puts user Deneme into your ignore list)
          ignore -r deneme      (removes user Deneme from your ignore list)
          ignore -f             (completely deletes your ignore list)
          ignore                (prints your ignore list to the screen)
~
End
Keyword fnotify~
Level 0
Text
Name       : fnotify
Synopsis   : fnotify -r|-f <forum name>

If you notify a forum using this command, when a note is left on that forum
you get a message indicating that a note is left on the board.

Examples: fnotify husky    (puts Husky forum in your forum notify list)
          fnotify -f       (completely deletes your forum notify list)
          fnotify -r husky (removes Husky forum from your forum notify list)
          fnotify          (prints your forum notify list to the screen)
~
End
Keyword notify~
Level 0
Text
Name       : notify
Synopsis   : notify -r|-f <nickname> <comment>

This list is also for your friends but only difference from friend command
is that a user in your notify list cannot send eXpress messages to you while
you are X disabled.  This is only used for notification when someone in this
list enters the BBS.  Optional part lets you write a comment upto 60
characters about the user.  You can use -r to remove a user from your notify
list.  Maximum number of users that you can put into your list is 50.
Option -f is used to completely delete your notify list.

Examples: notify deneme example (puts user Deneme in your notify list)
          notify -r deneme      (removes user Deneme from your notify list)
          notify -f             (completely deletes your notify list)
          notify                (prints your notify list to the screen)
~
End
Keyword friend~
Level 0
